# Self-Healing & Intelligence — Research Dossier

**Date:** 2026-06-26
**Upstream:** `diegosouzapw/OmniRoute` v3.8.36
**Fork:** `KooshaPari/OmniRoute`
**Status:** Pre-brainstorming evidence lock — no implementation yet, scope unconfirmed.

This file locks in **verified** facts about the upstream self-healing / routing /
quota / cost / model-intelligence surface so the brainstorming, spec, and
implementation work has zero cold-start cost. Every line is cited.

---

## 1. What already exists (verified, line-cited)

### 1.1 `SelfHealingManager` (single-class, in-memory)
`open-sse/services/autoCombo/selfHealing.ts:1-167`

- Auto-excludes a provider when its score drops below `0.2` (`EXCLUSION_THRESHOLD`, line 22).
- Cooldown escalation: doubles on repeated exclusion, capped at 30 min (`MAX_COOLDOWN_MS`, lines 19-20, 78-80).
- Re-admits at score ≥ `0.3` (`REENTRY_THRESHOLD`, line 21) once cooldown elapses.
- Probe flow: while excluded and circuit breaker is `HALF_OPEN`, allows a probe request; 3 successful probes fully re-admit (lines 67-72, 109-120).
- Incident mode: trips if >50% of providers are OPEN (`INCIDENT_MODE_THRESHOLD = 0.5`, lines 23, 125-135).
- State is **purely in-memory** (`private exclusions = new Map()`, line 26). Lost on restart.
- **No error-class granularity** — score is the only signal.
- **No anomaly detection** — purely threshold-based.
- **No persistence of learned priors** — only volatile `ExclusionEntry[]`.
- Singleton accessor: `getSelfHealingManager()` at line 164.

### 1.2 Pluggable routing strategies
`open-sse/services/autoCombo/routerStrategy.ts:1-331`

- `RouterStrategy` interface (lines 44-48): `name`, `description`, `select(pool, context) -> RoutingDecision`.
- Registered strategies (lines 288-303):
  - `rules` — 6-factor scoring wrapper
  - `cost` / `eco` (alias)
  - `latency` / `fast` (alias)
  - `sla-aware` / `sla` (alias) — checks p95 / error rate / cost SLOs
  - `lkgp` — last known good provider first
- `registerStrategy(name, impl)` (line 314) — extension point.
- `selectWithStrategy(pool, context, "rules")` — main entry point.
- None of these consume learned priors; scoring is point-in-time.

### 1.3 Quota cache (per-connection, with reset window)
`src/domain/quotaCache.ts:1-450`

- In-memory `Map<connectionId, QuotaCacheEntry>` (line 56).
- TTLs: active 5 min, exhausted 5 min (`ACTIVE_TTL_MS`, `EXHAUSTED_TTL_MS`, lines 48-49).
- Background tick every 60 s (`REFRESH_INTERVAL_MS`, line 51), max 5 concurrent refreshes (line 57).
- Persists snapshots via `saveQuotaSnapshot()` (line 20).
- `advancedWindowResetAt()` (lines 75-94) auto-advances past an expired `nextResetAt` — eagerly unblocks requests when the reset has passed but the background refresh hasn't run.
- `quotaSnapshotChanged()` (#4438 fix, lines 169-185) — pure function that returns true only on first observation or real change → prevents 400K+ no-op snapshot rows/day on idle accounts.
- **Gap:** `windowDurationMs` is referenced (line 36, line 245) but the corresponding DB column is **not present in any migration** (`grep -L "window_duration_ms" src/lib/db/migrations/*.sql` confirms). Field is dead code.

### 1.4 `model_intelligence` table — DORMANT
`src/lib/db/modelIntelligence.ts:1-232` + `src/lib/db/migrations/097_model_intelligence.sql`

- Table created in migration 097; PK = `(model, source, category)` (composite, WITHOUT ROWID).
- 3 sources: `user_override` (priority 1) > `arena_elo` (2) > `models_dev_tier` (3).
- 7 task categories: `coding | review | planning | analysis | debugging | documentation | default`.
- Full CRUD: `get`, `getBySource`, `upsert`, `delete`, `deleteExpired`, `deleteBySource`, `list`, `bulkUpsert`, `setUserFitnessOverrideEntry`, `deleteUserFitnessOverrideEntry`.
- Resolution chain helper `getResolvedTaskFitness(model, category)` at line 191.
- **Critical gap:** zero call sites. `grep -l "modelIntelligence\|ModelIntelligence" open-sse/services/autoCombo/taskFitness.ts src/domain/*.ts` returns 0 hits. Table exists but is **not wired into the live scorer**.

### 1.5 Resilience stack (4 layers)
`docs/architecture/RESILIENCE_GUIDE.md` (249 lines, v3.8.31, lastUpdated 2026-06-20)

1. **Provider circuit breaker** — `src/shared/utils/circuitBreaker.ts` — DB-backed `domain_circuit_breakers`, 4 states (CLOSED/DEGRADED/OPEN/HALF_OPEN). Trip codes `[408, 500, 502, 503, 504]`. OAuth: 5/8 failures/60s. API-key: 7/12/30s. Local: derived/2/15s.
2. **Connection cooldown** — `src/sse/services/auth.ts::markAccountUnavailable()`, exponential `baseCooldownMs * 2 ** failureIndex`, terminal states `banned | expired | credits_exhausted`.
3. **Model lockout** — in-memory `Map<provider:conn:model, ModelLockoutEntry>`. Settings persisted, state ephemeral.
4. **Quota-share concurrency (v3.8.36)** — per-connection `max_concurrent` semaphore + combo cooldown-aware retry bounded by `comboCooldownWait` (max 5s wait, 2 attempts, 8s budget).

All four are **reactive** — they respond to an error that already happened. None of them *predict* failure.

### 1.6 Cost surface
`src/domain/costRules.ts` (19.8 KB), pricing sync via `src/lib/pricingSync.ts` (LiteLLM source).

- `costPer1MTokens` is per-model, sourced from LiteLLM.
- No mechanism to derive $/MTok from a flat subscription.
- Provider connections table has no `monthly_cost` / `subscription_period` columns.

### 1.7 Data substrate already in place (lots of unused signal)
`src/lib/db/`:
- `quotaSnapshots.ts` — historical quota observations
- `usageLogs.ts`, `usageSummary.ts`, `usageAnalytics.ts`
- `providerStats.ts` (lines 29-67) — `getProviderCallStats()` / `getModelCallStats()` aggregate from `call_logs` (avg latency, success rate, total tokens)
- `quotaGroups.ts`, `quotaPools.ts`, `quotaModelCaps.ts`, `quotaConsumption.ts`
- `callLogStats.ts`, `compressionAnalytics.ts`, `compressionRunTelemetry.ts`
- `detailedLogs.ts`

The **history** is already being written. The **learning** layer that turns history into priors is missing.

### 1.8 E2E coverage today
`tests/e2e/`:
- `resilience-plan-alignment.spec.ts` (11.5 KB) — covers resilience plan UI alignment.
- `system-failover.test.ts` (25.4 KB) — failover behavior.
- `combos-flow.spec.ts` (20.9 KB) — combo flow.
- **No `self-healing.spec.ts` / `selfHealing.test.ts`** — `grep -r "selfHealing\|SelfHealing" tests/` returns 0 hits.
- **No `quota-learning.spec.ts` / `model-intelligence.spec.ts`.**

