## 2. The gap (what the user's task targets)

| User's ask | Today | Gap |
|---|---|---|
| Self-healing | In-memory `SelfHealingManager` with score-threshold + 3-probe re-admit | No persistence, no error-class granularity, no anomaly detection, no playbook |
| Learning quota reset times | `nextResetAt` cached per connection; 5-min refresh; auto-advance on past reset | Doesn't *learn* window length from history; `window_duration_ms` referenced but never persisted |
| Usage patterns by model | `providerStats` aggregates from `call_logs` | No bias injected into `RouterStrategy.select()` |
| User inputs monthly cost → derive $/MTok for cache r/w + I/O | `costPer1MTokens` from LiteLLM only | No subscription input; no cache r/w cost distinction; no derivation pipeline |
| Learn provider-model error types / latencies | `circuitBreaker.ts` only counts trip codes `[408, 500-504]` | No persistent error taxonomy; no per-(provider,model,error_class) failure rate |
| Optional LLM/agent learner | Skills + A2A + MCP infrastructure exists | No "analyst" skill that observes `detailed_logs` + `usage_logs` and emits healing actions |
| E2E | `resilience-plan-alignment.spec.ts` covers UI | No self-healing E2E, no quota-learning E2E |

